    public interface Observable<M>
    Simple interface for an observable object, with methods to add and remove observers expecting the applicable type of message.

    Unless otherwise specified, implementations should conceptually maintain the collection of observers according to the semantics of Set by object equality. Implementers should note that methods for weak observers must be reimplemented if anything other than default equality is used to denote membership.

      • addWeakObserver

        default <O> boolean addWeakObserver(O owner,
                                    Function<? super O,Consumer<? super M>> observer)
        Observers added will receive messages from this Observable. A weak observer will be removed automatically once the given owner is available for garbage collection.

        Only one weak observer can be registered for any given owner.

        The observer itself must be given in the form of a function applicable to the owner to ensure it does not create a reference to the owner and prevent garbage collection.

        Type Parameters:
        O - The type of the owner
        Parameters:
        observer - An observer to add
        owner - The owner of the observer
        Returns:
        True if the observer was successfully added, false otherwise.

      • removeWeakObserver

        default boolean removeWeakObserver(Object owner)
        Remove any observer from this Observable which has the given owner. Observers added without an explicitly given owner are considered to be owned by themselves.

        Only one weak observer can be registered for any given owner.

        Parameters:
        owner - An observer to remove, or an owner whose observer is to be removed
        Returns:
        True if the observer was successfully removed, false otherwise
